            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". To give you an idea of how that stacks up to another challenging year, for the 2020 model year GM made just 20,368 Corvettes. However, for 2019 there were 34,822 Corvettes made, so if this report is accurate, GM isn’t that far off regular production figures. Keep in mind the C8 Corvette no doubt is getting computer chips and other components which are being diverted from other, less-profitable vehicles.",
